task.summary: Added Status Request and Response Added Status option to the POS form. Added a JSON library to the project for easier parsing of responses.
Handled blank response fields so the response doesn't fail. Changed the Response Text Area to just append, and added a clear text area button. Deleted obsolete code from the PCEFTPOSMsg class.
Added GetLastTransaction and ReprintReceipt. Added Request options combobox to change request types i.e purchase/refund/cashout, settlement/presettlment/lastsettlement etc.
Added a check for 'Get Last' or 'Reprint Last' receipt
Added some regions to make code navigation a bit easier. Updated readme
Added in an Async socket class and window that uses it.

Added a new AsyncSocket class and Control. Added EFTControlPanel Request and Response because opening the control panel through the Client GUI sent a response to the socket that it didn't know how to handle. Added SetDialog Request and Response. Updated the readme
Changed access modifiers to some class properties. Implemented SetDialogRequest in UI. Update readme.
Updated the messageParser to grab the settlementDate from GetLastTransactionResponse.
Trimmed the purchaseAnalysisData on the parser so we don't get a giant string of null characters in the response object.
Rejiggered the manifest so hopefully it builds an executable .jar. It works (it displays the GUI at least) on the raspberry pi. Rejiggered the readme for readability.
Added ability to change socket connections. Does not work with synchronous PCEFTPOSControl class. Completely dead. Changed look and feel of the asyncWindow

V4 client connection was sending a #0005 message to client on connection, and receiving a Pinpad Busy response that the Java code wasn't dealing with. So added in a response class and now the POS will display the Pinpad busy message instead of closing the socket.
